        <section id="lesson2" class="lesson">
            <h2>Lesson 2: Variables and Data Types</h2>
            <p>In this lesson, we will learn about variables and different data types in Python. Variables store data, and Python has several built-in data types to choose from.</p>
            <h3>Variable Assignment</h3>
            <p>In Python, you can assign a value to a variable as follows:</p>
            <pre><code>age = 25</code></pre>
            <p>The variable <strong>age</strong> now holds the value 25. Python supports different data types such as:</p>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>int</strong>: Integer values</li>
                <li><strong>float</strong>: Decimal values</li>
                <li><strong>str</strong>: String values</li>
                <li><strong>bool</strong>: Boolean values (True or False)</li>
            </ul>
    
           
        </section>
    
        <section id="lesson3" class="lesson">
            <h2>Lesson 3: Functions</h2>
            <p>In this lesson, we will learn how to define and use functions in Python to organize code and avoid repetition.</p>
            <h3>Defining a Function</h3>
            <p>Functions are defined using the <strong>def</strong> keyword:</p>
            <pre><code>def greet(name):
        print("Hello, " + name)
    
    greet("Alice")</code></pre>
            <p>This function takes one parameter <strong>name</strong> and prints a greeting. In the above code, the function <strong>greet()</strong> is called with the argument "Alice", which will output "Hello, Alice".</p>
            
